Job Description
Mackinnon Bruce is working on behalf of a specialized oilfield service company based in the United Arab Emirates. The company has grown to become the leading regional provider of oilfield services in the Middle East with over 2,000 employees working across more than 20 countries.
As a provider of quality oilfield services and a growing client base in the Middle East they are now looking to add an experienced reservoir engineer to their Abu Dhabi based team who will be reporting directly to the Sales Manager.
Responsibilities:
Manage production and process logging needs for each client
Work alone or with other reservoir engineers as needed
Capable of handling a large amount of responsibility with limited supervision
Extensive travel within the Middle East and North Africa to meet clients
Qualifications:
B.Sc in Petroleum Engineering
5-7 years relevant industry experience with oilfield service company
Experience with Emeraude production logging software essential
Extensive reservoir production and process logging
Excellent organizational and communication skills
Ability to take part in a multicultural team
Very good language skills in English (written and oral)
My client offers excellent career development opportunities for growth and a competitive annual salary plus additional benefits.
Mackinnon Bruce International is a specialist recruitment company in the Energy sector with a team dedicated to the Oil and Gas market. We have extensive links with market leading organisations in numerous locations for positions at a Mid-Senior level.
Qualifications
Bachelors Degree or equivalent
